283
00:15:43,640 --> 00:15:45,280
How did she pick a fight with you?

284
00:15:45,280 --> 00:15:47,810
She insisted my paintings weren't done by me.

285
00:15:48,400 --> 00:15:49,320
Let me check.

286
00:15:51,160 --> 00:15:51,960
Jiang Xiaoyu.

287
00:15:52,480 --> 00:15:53,880
Famous blogger.

288
00:15:54,600 --> 00:15:57,600
The youngest PhD student at Southeast Art Academy.

289
00:15:58,880 --> 00:16:00,400
She has so many followers.

290
00:16:00,680 --> 00:16:02,400
Famous art critic.

291
00:16:03,120 --> 00:16:04,320
Quite a lot of titles.

292
00:16:04,440 --> 00:16:05,760
So many followers.

293
00:16:06,160 --> 00:16:06,680
Yes.

294
00:16:06,800 --> 00:16:09,720
She's what they call a big influencer on Weibo, right?

295
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:10,920
I'm surprised you know about influencers.

296
00:16:10,920 --> 00:16:12,280
Well, take a look.

297
00:16:13,360 --> 00:16:14,360
This is serious.

298
00:16:14,840 --> 00:16:15,640
With so many followers,

299
00:16:15,640 --> 00:16:17,440
isn't it good that she's paying attention to you?

300
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:18,680
What's good about it?

301
00:16:19,160 --> 00:16:22,220
If she criticizes me once, it would be a disaster for me.

302
00:16:22,560 --> 00:16:24,120
I hate people like her.

303
00:16:24,280 --> 00:16:25,040
Tell me,

304
00:16:25,160 --> 00:16:27,200
why should her words be considered authoritative?

305
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:29,080
How can she represent authority?

306
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:30,520
But she's a PhD.

307
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:32,320
PhD? So what?

308
00:16:32,440 --> 00:16:34,570
These days post-docs are everywhere.

309
00:16:35,680 --> 00:16:37,360
Besides, she called me a fraud.

310
00:16:37,360 --> 00:16:39,400
Does that automatically make me one?

311
00:16:39,400 --> 00:16:40,730
I need to argue with her.

312
00:16:41,920 --> 00:16:43,250
Forget it. Don't reply.

313
00:16:44,440 --> 00:16:46,960
I'm asking her why her words should be considered authoritative.

314
00:16:46,960 --> 00:16:48,760
It seems one-sided to me.

315
00:16:50,280 --> 00:16:51,680
Isn't she a PhD?

316
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:00,200
She replied.

317
00:17:02,080 --> 00:17:05,480
Let the work speak for itself. What's fake can't become real.

318
00:17:06,040 --> 00:17:08,200
This is getting heated. Let it go.

319
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:13,000
Her followers left comments for me.

320
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:15,520
Saying I'm trying to use her to get famous.

321
00:17:15,520 --> 00:17:16,960
What kind of situation is this?

322
00:17:16,960 --> 00:17:18,920
I mean, do her fans have any brains?

323
00:17:19,839 --> 00:17:22,480
My grades at the art academy were outstanding.

324
00:17:22,480 --> 00:17:26,410
CrystalGlasses00: That's a huge difference! They're clearly lying!

325
00:17:31,320 --> 00:17:32,920
She's a Weibo celebrity.

326
00:17:33,040 --> 00:17:34,320
She gets hundreds of comments instantly.

327
00:17:34,320 --> 00:17:35,320
If she says anything negative about you,

328
00:17:35,320 --> 00:17:36,880
you won't be able to sell any of your paintings.

329
00:17:36,880 --> 00:17:39,120
Do you realize what time it is? This is a critical period.

330
00:17:39,120 --> 00:17:40,640
We're in the middle of a lawsuit.

331
00:17:40,640 --> 00:17:41,800
It could very well affect

332
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:43,960
the outcome of the case. Do you understand?

333
00:17:43,960 --> 00:17:45,080
That's exactly why

334
00:17:45,200 --> 00:17:47,130
I need to argue with her about this.

335
00:17:47,880 --> 00:17:48,920
Mom is so stubborn.

336
00:17:48,920 --> 00:17:50,250
Hitting her won't help.

337
00:17:54,760 --> 00:17:56,080
Hey, Jiang Xiaoyu.

338
00:17:56,440 --> 00:17:57,700
I want to meet with you.

339
00:17:58,360 --> 00:17:59,520
Do you dare to come?

340
00:18:10,840 --> 00:18:12,300
You're quite persistent.

341
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:15,260
I can't stand being wrongly accused.

342
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:21,320
Can I take a photo?

343
00:18:21,840 --> 00:18:22,640
Of course.

344
00:18:28,640 --> 00:18:30,440
Can I post this painting online?

345
00:18:30,680 --> 00:18:31,760
Whatever.

346
00:18:35,760 --> 00:18:36,820
What are you doing?

347
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:40,530
I told you, what's fake can't become real.

348
00:18:42,040 --> 00:18:43,700
All these paintings are mine.

349
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:45,130
Do you think this one

350
00:18:45,240 --> 00:18:46,770
is the same as those others?

351
00:18:47,720 --> 00:18:49,440
How can I prove you wrong?

352
00:18:49,840 --> 00:18:51,040
Don't bother, okay?

353
00:19:04,480 --> 00:19:06,140
Being cheerful is beautiful.

354
00:19:37,400 --> 00:19:39,460
Tell me, what exactly is the problem?

355
00:19:39,480 --> 00:19:40,280
The problem is

356
00:19:40,360 --> 00:19:42,760
these paintings weren't done by you at all.

357
00:19:42,920 --> 00:19:44,640
How can I prove you wrong?

358
00:19:45,160 --> 00:19:46,290
Don't bother, okay?

359
00:19:48,880 --> 00:19:50,160
Tomorrow at 9 a.m.

360
00:19:50,480 --> 00:19:52,040
I'll be waiting for you here.

361
00:19:52,040 --> 00:19:54,000
I really don't have time to keep playing this game.

362
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:54,880
Goodbye.

363
00:19:55,480 --> 00:19:56,400
You must come.

364
00:20:30,040 --> 00:20:30,960
Have you heard?

365
00:20:32,360 --> 00:20:33,200
About what?

366
00:20:34,080 --> 00:20:35,740
Wan Xinxin has become famous.

367
00:20:36,880 --> 00:20:37,840
What happened?

368
00:20:38,720 --> 00:20:40,360
Didn't she want to open an art gallery?

369
00:20:40,360 --> 00:20:41,720
But she was torn apart

370
00:20:41,840 --> 00:20:43,280
by a famous critic.

371
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:46,760
I see.

372
00:20:47,680 --> 00:20:49,880
Her lawyer must have told her

373
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:51,160
that she needs legitimate income

374
00:20:51,160 --> 00:20:52,720
to win custody of her child.

375
00:20:53,320 --> 00:20:55,080
But her gallery hasn't even opened yet

376
00:20:55,080 --> 00:20:56,760
and her reputation is already so bad.

377
00:20:56,760 --> 00:20:58,620
She's just waiting to lose money.

378
00:21:00,040 --> 00:21:01,880
This is good news for me.

379
00:21:02,160 --> 00:21:04,090
I'll definitely win this lawsuit.

380
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:05,800
Then I'll take this child

381
00:21:05,840 --> 00:21:07,960
with me to America to show my mother.

382
00:21:08,240 --> 00:21:10,640
My mother might not acknowledge me as her son,

383
00:21:10,640 --> 00:21:12,560
but she can't deny her grandson.

384
00:21:14,720 --> 00:21:18,680
Now whoever has custody of the child

385
00:21:19,720 --> 00:21:21,920
will get that money.

386
00:21:23,280 --> 00:21:25,280
Never mind her lousy lawyer.

387
00:21:25,640 --> 00:21:28,440
Just the fact that she can't afford to raise the child

388
00:21:28,440 --> 00:21:30,170
means we're guaranteed to win.

389
00:21:31,640 --> 00:21:32,680
Wan Xinxin.

390
00:21:33,520 --> 00:21:35,650
This gallery will be yours from now on.

391
00:21:36,480 --> 00:21:37,120
I feel like

392
00:21:37,240 --> 00:21:39,040
I'm just one big joke.

393
00:21:40,320 --> 00:21:41,920
How could you be a joke?

394
00:21:42,280 --> 00:21:43,920
Let me tell you, you're my biggest investment.

395
00:21:43,920 --> 00:21:45,360
Xiao Ruan who rents from me told me

396
00:21:45,360 --> 00:21:46,760
that this art district has produced masters before.

397
00:21:46,760 --> 00:21:48,320
You're going to be a future master.

398
00:21:48,320 --> 00:21:49,360
Me, a master?

399
00:21:49,640 --> 00:21:50,700
Don't joke around.

400
00:21:50,760 --> 00:21:52,160
Have you ever seen a master who hasn't even debuted yet,

401
00:21:52,160 --> 00:21:53,000
who before creating anything

402
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:55,330
is already being criticized everywhere?

403
00:21:56,680 --> 00:21:58,140
Everything has two sides.

404
00:21:58,200 --> 00:21:59,000
Well,

405
00:21:59,120 --> 00:22:00,980
you can turn defeat into victory.

406
00:22:01,720 --> 00:22:02,800
Old friend,

407
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:05,160
let's just give up this gallery.

408
00:22:05,720 --> 00:22:07,600
I'm just a money-losing investment.

409
00:22:07,600 --> 00:22:08,520
No.

410
00:22:08,640 --> 00:22:09,360
I don't want to hear that.

411
00:22:09,360 --> 00:22:10,920
Really, I'm begging you.

412
00:22:12,280 --> 00:22:14,280
It's not as simple as just giving up.

413
00:22:14,360 --> 00:22:15,680
The money's been paid and can't be refunded.

414
00:22:15,680 --> 00:22:18,540
Whether you can do it or not, you have to make it work.

415
00:22:19,320 --> 00:22:21,080
I don't even believe in myself.

416
00:22:21,240 --> 00:22:23,080
I'll definitely disappoint you.

417
00:22:23,080 --> 00:22:24,760
You've never disappointed me.

418
00:22:24,760 --> 00:22:26,420
You've only scared me before.

419
00:22:27,320 --> 00:22:28,720
Come, let's drink first.

420
00:22:29,160 --> 00:22:31,560
Well, I can only thank you.

421
00:22:32,280 --> 00:22:33,540
When I win the lawsuit,

422
00:22:34,040 --> 00:22:35,370
I'll give myself to you.

423
00:22:41,400 --> 00:22:42,660
What's with that face?

424
00:22:44,080 --> 00:22:45,880
Everything for my dear brother.

425
00:22:46,680 --> 00:22:47,740
I'll give it my all.

426
00:23:02,720 --> 00:23:04,040
Sis, thank you for your hard work.

427
00:23:04,040 --> 00:23:04,840
It's nothing.

428
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:05,960
Huaming,

429
00:23:06,160 --> 00:23:08,090
you can't just let her have her way.

430
00:23:08,320 --> 00:23:09,520
If this goes to court,

431
00:23:09,720 --> 00:23:11,040
whether she can support the child

432
00:23:11,040 --> 00:23:12,160
is what matters most.

433
00:23:12,160 --> 00:23:13,080
Opening an art gallery?

434
00:23:13,080 --> 00:23:14,600
When will that ever make money?

435
00:23:14,600 --> 00:23:15,600
You'd be better off

436
00:23:15,600 --> 00:23:17,120
investing in something else.

437
00:23:17,120 --> 00:23:18,720
Sis, what should I invest in?

438
00:23:18,880 --> 00:23:19,920
Open a bun shop.

439
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:22,130
A bun shop makes money from day one.

440
00:23:22,520 --> 00:23:24,450
Running a bun shop requires skills

441
00:23:24,520 --> 00:23:25,640
that Xinxin can't handle.

442
00:23:25,640 --> 00:23:26,920
What can't I handle?

443
00:23:27,280 --> 00:23:28,120
Sister was just saying...

444
00:23:28,120 --> 00:23:29,280
Fine, you two talk it out.

445
00:23:29,280 --> 00:23:31,760
Sister was saying you should focus on your painting.

446
00:23:31,760 --> 00:23:32,520
We're open!

447
00:23:34,720 --> 00:23:35,680
What are you doing here?

448
00:23:35,680 --> 00:23:37,480
Look at you, all talented and painting now.

449
00:23:37,480 --> 00:23:39,760
What's it to you? Is it any of your business?

450
00:23:39,760 --> 00:23:41,220
Business is booming, huh?

451
00:23:42,240 --> 00:23:43,570
I want to buy a painting.

452
00:23:43,680 --> 00:23:44,440
Let me see.

453
00:23:44,560 --> 00:23:45,520
100, 5.

454
00:23:46,480 --> 00:23:48,880
107. That should be enough to buy one of your paintings.

455
00:23:48,880 --> 00:23:51,880
Qin Gang, you're deliberately trying to cause trouble, aren't you?

456
00:23:51,880 --> 00:23:52,800
No, I'm just...

457
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:54,480
supporting your first sale of the day.

458
00:23:54,480 --> 00:23:55,320
No.

459
00:23:56,000 --> 00:23:58,640
Look, it's your opening day. It's auspicious,

460
00:23:59,040 --> 00:23:59,600
isn't it?

461
00:23:59,800 --> 00:24:01,920
Come on, Mr. Qin is just helping with your first sale.

462
00:24:01,920 --> 00:24:02,980
That's nice of him.

463
00:24:03,080 --> 00:24:05,280
It will help with your future business.

464
00:24:05,280 --> 00:24:06,280
Thank you, Mr. Qin.

465
00:24:06,280 --> 00:24:07,760
However, Mr. Qin,

466
00:24:08,160 --> 00:24:10,240
our Xinxin here is a renowned female artist.

467
00:24:10,240 --> 00:24:12,880
So this amount of money won't actually buy one of her paintings.

468
00:24:12,880 --> 00:24:15,240
100, 5, 1, 2...

469
00:24:15,400 --> 00:24:16,320
107 yuan.

470
00:24:16,680 --> 00:24:17,740
Just wait a moment.

471
00:24:18,040 --> 00:24:19,680
If you pay, you get to take a painting.

472
00:24:19,680 --> 00:24:21,080
See how reasonable he is?

473
00:24:21,320 --> 00:24:23,520
A good opening brings prosperity. Harmony brings wealth.

474
00:24:23,520 --> 00:24:24,920
Why are you so hot-tempered?

475
00:24:24,920 --> 00:24:26,080
How will you get any customers?

476
00:24:26,080 --> 00:24:27,800
With your intelligence, shouldn't you be offering 250?

477
00:24:27,800 --> 00:24:29,440
You don't even meet that standard yet.

478
00:24:29,440 --> 00:24:30,920
No, no. I'm talking about you.

479
00:24:30,920 --> 00:24:31,800
I'm talking about you.

480
00:24:31,800 --> 00:24:32,260
Mr. Qin.

481
00:24:32,280 --> 00:24:33,040
I'm talking about you.

482
00:24:33,040 --> 00:24:35,100
Mr. Qin. I'm also an amateur painter.

483
00:24:35,640 --> 00:24:37,400
It's just that my paintings aren't very valuable.

484
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:38,760
But with this money of yours,

485
00:24:38,760 --> 00:24:40,480
you could buy a painting like this.

486
00:24:40,480 --> 00:24:43,000
Qin Gang.

487
00:24:45,320 --> 00:24:47,120
Today, let me make my first sale.

488
00:24:52,480 --> 00:24:54,080
Is this all you two are capable of?

489
00:24:54,080 --> 00:24:55,480
Yes, that's all we've got.

490
00:24:55,480 --> 00:24:57,440
You think opening an art gallery will help you win the case?

491
00:24:57,440 --> 00:24:58,560
Keep dreaming.

492
00:24:59,200 --> 00:25:00,960
Let me tell you what I'm most worried about.

493
00:25:00,960 --> 00:25:03,080
It's that when Xiaobao grows up, he'll be mocked

494
00:25:03,080 --> 00:25:05,200
because his mother is a street artist

495
00:25:05,280 --> 00:25:06,080
and a fraud.

496
00:25:06,320 --> 00:25:08,280
Still better than having a jerk for a father, isn't it?

497
00:25:08,280 --> 00:25:09,280
Stop it, please.

498
00:25:09,680 --> 00:25:10,320
Mr. Qin.

499
00:25:10,480 --> 00:25:12,000
Well, let's talk this through calmly.

500
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:14,160
Even if you want to sue, there's no need for bad blood.

501
00:25:14,160 --> 00:25:14,800
Well...

502
00:25:14,920 --> 00:25:15,480
Sis.

503
00:25:16,080 --> 00:25:17,360
Look, um...

504
00:25:17,720 --> 00:25:20,120
We just opened and things aren't perfect yet.

505
00:25:20,120 --> 00:25:22,250
Come back next time. Let me see you out.

506
00:25:22,600 --> 00:25:23,800
We'll see about that.

507
00:25:23,800 --> 00:25:24,930
Just get out of here.

508
00:25:30,960 --> 00:25:32,160
Does it look like you?

509
00:25:35,600 --> 00:25:36,400
Qin Gang,

510
00:25:36,680 --> 00:25:38,680
don't you want your self-portrait?

511
00:25:38,720 --> 00:25:41,320
You can take this home to ward off evil spirits.

512
00:25:45,120 --> 00:25:46,180
Xinxin, come here.

513
00:25:46,840 --> 00:25:47,720
Come here.

514
00:25:55,080 --> 00:25:58,610
Congratulations on the grand opening of Wan Xinxin's gallery.

515
00:26:16,200 --> 00:26:17,960
Xinxin, even when you're right, you should be gracious.

516
00:26:17,960 --> 00:26:19,960
Why do you have to argue with people?

517
00:26:20,840 --> 00:26:21,960
Didn't you say

518
00:26:22,160 --> 00:26:23,760
I should thank my enemies?

519
00:26:24,600 --> 00:26:25,840
I can't believe this Jiang Xiaoyu.

520
00:26:25,840 --> 00:26:28,170
I have to fight her to the bitter end today.

521
00:26:28,320 --> 00:26:29,960
Do you know what I admire most about you?

522
00:26:29,960 --> 00:26:32,320
This resilient spirit that can't be beaten down.

523
00:26:32,320 --> 00:26:33,450
I bow to you for that.

524
00:26:37,920 --> 00:26:38,760
I'll get it.

525
00:26:39,880 --> 00:26:40,720
Coming.

526
00:26:43,640 --> 00:26:44,360
Hello.

527
00:26:44,440 --> 00:26:45,700
Delivery for Miss Wan.

528
00:26:45,720 --> 00:26:46,280
Who?

529
00:26:46,680 --> 00:26:47,440
Miss Wan.

530
00:26:47,560 --> 00:26:48,160
Okay.

531
00:26:50,280 --> 00:26:51,140
Your delivery.

532
00:27:06,760 --> 00:27:07,520
What is it?

533
00:27:10,320 --> 00:27:11,320
A summons.

534
00:27:11,720 --> 00:27:13,650
The court hearing is next Tuesday.

535
00:27:20,320 --> 00:27:21,560
Don't sigh like that.

536
00:27:22,480 --> 00:27:24,880
What's meant to come will come eventually.

537
00:27:27,200 --> 00:27:28,000
Do you know why

538
00:27:28,040 --> 00:27:30,120
I'm fighting so hard with this Jiang Xiaoyu?

539
00:27:30,120 --> 00:27:31,320
Because she's right.

540
00:27:31,880 --> 00:27:33,720
These paintings aren't mine.

541
00:27:34,120 --> 00:27:36,080
At least not painted by who I am now.

542
00:27:36,600 --> 00:27:38,480
I hate it when she says things like that,

543
00:27:38,480 --> 00:27:40,080
but I can't argue against it.

544
00:27:40,880 --> 00:27:42,320
Everything is wrong.

545
00:27:42,560 --> 00:27:45,120
Nothing is right. It's all terribly wrong.

546
00:27:49,040 --> 00:27:50,040
Xinxin.

547
00:27:50,720 --> 00:27:52,650
Creative work needs inspiration.

548
00:27:52,960 --> 00:27:54,560
Don't worry. Take your time.

549
00:27:54,640 --> 00:27:56,080
No, how can I take my time?

550
00:27:56,240 --> 00:27:59,000
I don't have time. The hearing is next Tuesday.

551
00:27:59,120 --> 00:28:00,320
When the judge asks me

552
00:28:00,440 --> 00:28:02,080
how I plan to support my child,

553
00:28:02,080 --> 00:28:03,000
what am I supposed to say?

554
00:28:03,000 --> 00:28:06,660
That I rely on a gallery that can't sell paintings and loses money?

555
00:28:09,160 --> 00:28:11,200
The key issue is that I'm being flooded with negative comments online.

556
00:28:11,200 --> 00:28:12,520
Do you think the judge will award custody

557
00:28:12,520 --> 00:28:14,650
to someone who's being called a fraud?

558
00:28:26,760 --> 00:28:28,000
She replied.

559
00:28:34,280 --> 00:28:35,880
She's crazy.

560
00:28:36,760 --> 00:28:37,880
She talked about Mr. Qin like that.

